{"/service/ndnp/kyu/batch_kyu_mastiff_ver02/data/sn86069021/0051699762A/1908052201/0401.xml":{"full_text":"T\ni\nTHE\nFALMOUTH KENTUCKY FRIDAY MAY 22 1908\nVOLUME 1\ne\ni1\n:i\nit?\nI\nX\nj\nA Statement\nThat our position may be fairly nd\nclearly nnderatood we wish toatate that\nthe District Board of the Barley Tobac\nco Society and the Board of Control of\nPendleton County have each ordered\ncut for inspection and delivery to Fal\nmouth and Cincinnati all Equity tobac\nco in this county thus for sold All\nhandlers in the county with the excep\ntion of Ur Ewing at Morgan have\ncomplied with these rulings The buy\ners all refuse to go to other points to\ninspect their purchases as the quanti\nties axe too small to justify the trouble\nand expense The Inspecting Commit-\ntee is however authorised to pay dray\nage to from the depot and it is now up\nto the owners of this tobacco at Morgan\nto decide whether or not they will' hold\nit there or ship it to one of the above\nnamed places for inspection and deliv\nery as Mr Ewing claims they (the ow\nners) are opposed to incurring this ex-\nThe owners of the tobacco stored at\nMorgan must see that in order to re\nceive pay for this tobacco it must be\nsent to one of the above named places\nfor inspection The buyers positively\nrefuse to go to any other point to make\nan inspection and one of the largest\nbuyers states that he will not buy any\nmore tobacco in the county unless it is\ndelivered to one of the above named\nplaces\nIt is hoped that all sold tobacco will\nbe delivered within the next ten days\nand payment will speedily follow\nBoard of Control\nPendleton County\ny\nA lie Nailed\nA dispatch from Corinth in Sunday's\nEnquirer states that tobacco beds were\ndestroyed by night riders on three\nfarms in Scott county Friday night of\nlast week in three different sections of\n1 that county The dispatch also states\nthat the night riders were from Pendle\nton county This is a lie out of the\nwhole doth In the first place it was\nimpossible for any body of men to have\ncovered the territory mentioned and\nespecially if they were from this eoun\nty The correspondent might as well\nhave said the night riders came from\nAlaska and been about -as xorrect\nPeople at a distance will read it and\ntake it to be true and the disgrace will\nwrongfully rest on our shoulders The\ncorrespondent doubtless knew where\nthe raiders came from and wanted to\nshield them and when he said they\nhailed from Pendleton he did us a great\nhijweHiMi-\nWe have had but little night riding\nin this county and the less we have the\nbetter Our people are not in favor of\nnight riding for it- is lawlessness pure\nand simple and the persons who en\ngage in the cowardly crimes that have\ndisgraced bur state have no right to\nshelter themselves behind the cause of\nthe tobacco grower If any person en\ngaged in these raids ia justifying him\nself therefor upon the ground that he\nis aiding the tobacco growers in their\ni fight for living prices for their product\nhe is hugging delusion to his bosom\nThe greatest enemy of the association\nis the man who is taking part in the\nlawless raids\nNotice to Fishermen\nLak Grant at Butler will open up\nfor fishing on Saturday May 90th and\nMr Grant is making arrangements to\nentertain a very large number of fish\nermen The lake and grounds are\neven more beautiful this year than\never before and the lake is well\nstocked with fish No one will he al\nlowed on the grounds except they are\nthere for business The charge of \u00a35\nwih for non-fishermen will be in\nvogue again this year\nFbr further particulars addrem A J\nGrant Butler Ky\nWill Groff ord in Trouble\nA pistol battle over a horse deal in\nHamilton county back of Cincinnati\non Tuesday resulted in Charles Jones\nJr being killed and several men\nwounded Tom Jones and Will Crof\nford are under arrest 1\nWill Crofford left Falmouth last\nSunday There is a warrant here for\nCroff ord\u2019s arrest for selling whisky in\nlocal option territory\nJodgment For Damages\nThe Bracken County Board of Con\ntrol sued Ben and Jacob Courts in the\nBracken Quarterly Court for damages\nfor selling tobacco pledged to the So\nciety In one ease a jury gave a verdict for\n966 damages and far the other tried be\nfore Judge Bradford judgment for $57\nwas given The costs added will make\nit cost the Courts Brothers about 976\neach for having disposed of pooled to-\nHOGWALLOW NEWS\nFna Haowillow Kanteckian\nFit Smith has bought him a clock to\nregulate his watch with'\nDock Hocks spent yesterday at Tick\nville and came in a dime of purchasing\na new pair of shoes\nThe Hog Ford preacher aims to start\na protracted meeting aa soon as the\nfinancial panic blows over\nStandard Hancock has moved into\nour immediate midst and will locate\nnear the mulberry tree on Musket\nRidge\nMiss Rosyola Mosely fell from her\ntall yellow horse yesterday and\nknocked the breath out of her accor\ndeon There is now only one prisoner in the\njail at Bounding Billows and it is now\nrumored that he intends to get out as\nsoon as he finishes his term\nThe mail carrier ia rushing his horse\nover the route between here andTick\nvilie now in order to gain enough time\nto get a day off next July\nAs an inducement to get his cow to\ncome up late every evening Jefferson\nPotlocks has placed a bunch of sorghum\nstalks just out of her reach at the\nstable\nTobe Mosely has had a picture made\nof his four dawgs and they are very\nlifelike He says aa soon as he gets\nable he is going to have his wife's pic\nture made\nAtlas Peck caught a nice wooden leg\nin the drift that came down Gander\ncreek lost week and ia very proud of\nit He says he will save it and sell it\nwhen the next war comes up\nFletcher Kenstep has one of the\nspottedest dawgs ever seen in this lo\ncality The spots cover hia body ex\ntend out to the end of hia tail and a\nfew of the largest ones hang off and\ndrag the ground\nMiss Fruxie Allsop has just arrived\nback-from a pleasant stay at Buxzatd\nKnob She is so charmed with the\nplace that she has been inspired to\nwrite an obituary for the -postmaster\nwho recently died there -1 i\nSndij School Census\nThe ladies who have been appointed\nby the Sunday Schools of the city to\ntake the Sunday School census and also\nto ascertain to what church the older\nmembers of the family belong have\nbeen at work this week A house to\nhouse canvas is being made They\nleave the following invitation at each\nhome:-\nWe eome today with a cordial in\nvitation to you from every Sunday\nSchool and-church in this community\nIf you attend the services of the church\nand Sunday School of your choice reg\nularly all extend greetings if you do\nnot all join in a most earnest request\nthat you do aa We want to assure you\na hearty welcome\u201d\nwm Build New Ban\nO L Mains the hustling saw-mill\nman has his outfit on the place of Wal\nter Snodgrass and is cutting the lumber\nfor a large feed and tobacco barn\nwhich Mr Snodgrass expects to erect\nIn the near future Mr Mains says he\nhas all the work contracted for that he\nwill be able to get out this summer\nReleased From The Pea\nJerry McCarthy a veteran of the\ncivil war convicted about 16 months\nago in the Circuit Court here for rob\nbing the residence of Ethel Lowe pear\nMorgan and given two years in the\npen was released last week He was\narrested in Covington Tuesday for\ndrunkeness He took a pledge not to\ndrink any more during life and was\nreleased\nSoldiers Again\nTuesday afternoon about 6:00 o'clock\n8 soldiers arrived in Falmouth from the\ndirection of Bracken county They re\nmained until Wednesday and took their\ndeparture for the parts unknown They\nhad the appearance of haring been out\nfor some time as their horses were tired\nand worn out\nHis Job Not Envied\nRobert Sorrell the old Butler boy\nwho is sheriff of Ottawa eounty Okla\nis probably destined to officiate at the\nfirst legal hanging in the new state of\nnnimiii aa June 26th has been set as\nthe day John Hopkins will be hanged\nfor murder\u2014 Butler Reformer\nFrigktfollj Scalded\nThe little 8-year-old daughter of Mrs\nKate Cummins met with very pain\nful accident on laat Sunday The child\nupset a tea pot filled with boiling liquid\nand frightfully scalded her limb from\nthe hip down\nA Crashing Defeat\nThe Bulter High School boys defeated\nthe Falmouth High School team last\nSaturday afternoon at the Boston Sta\ntion grounds in a score of 27 to 2\nThe report comes from ah eye wit\nness that it was the most unfair game\nhe ever saw He said the Butler team\ndid all the batting and the Falmouth\nboys chasod the balls until their tongues\nhung out Two and three-base hits\ncame thick and fast and home runs be\ncame very numerous the latter part of\nthe game It waa to have been a nine\ninning go but a fortunate thing hap\npened when one of the Butler boys hit\nthe sphere so hard that the game was\ncalled on account of \"lost ball\" This\nwas a lucky thing for our boys or they\nmight have been chasing the balls yet\nThe Butler lads broke all their bats but\none and it was considerably \"damaged\nThis bat will be stored in the -archives\nof the Public School building os ah in\nstrument of durability there to be\nviewed by the victorious posterity It\nwas a lop-aided slugging match\nThe same team will be invited to Fal\nmouth some time in the near future to\nplay another game Our boys say they\nwill play their \u201cbest\" next time and\ntry to recover lost laurels\u2019 v\n\"By special request\" we omit the\nnames of those who took part in the\ngame 1\nNeave 26 Oklahoma Giants 11\nIn the game last Saturday between\ntho Neave Sluggers and Oklahoma\nGiants the former won out in a score\nof 28 to 11 It was an exciting game\nfrom start to finish The boys were\nnot in good practice and this accounts\nfor big score There is some fine ball\ntimber at Neave and a little warm\nweather and practice will develope it\nJesse Cummins and Earl Smith were in\nthe points for Neave and James Light\nner and Tom Hotfoot were the battery\nfor Oklahoma and Joe Neave Empire\nTom Hotfoot is considered a finished\nball player but the season was a little\ntoo young to give a fast exhibition of\nhis ability When he does return to\nform brilliant work will be seen on the\ndiamond\nPreparing Tim Grounds\nThe btise ball enthniaf ts of Fhlmouth\nhave taken on new life The diamond\nat the Fair grounds- is being put in\nshape and lovers of the national sport\nmay look for some good games this\nsummer All the surrounding towns\nand villages are organising ball teams\nand the local club will take them in on\ndue season\nThe boys are circulating a subscrip\ntion paper to raise funds for uniform\netc and the citizens are giving liberal\nly'\nDouble Header\nThere will be two games of ball at\nNeave Saturday May 23 McKinneys\nbury and Powersville will both take a\nwhack at Neave Game called at 2:30\nJoe Lacey will do the twirling for\nNeave\nNotice Goforth Juniors\nAll members of the Goforth Council\nNo 175 Jr O U A M are requested\nto meet at their hall next Tuesday even\ning at 8 o\u2019clock Important business\nBy request of Councilor\nNotice D of A\u2019s!\n9 i\nIt is requested that a full attendance\nof the members of the D of A Lodge\nbe present at the next regular meeting\nMay 2$ as there is business of impor\ntance to be transacted By order of\nMrs Leona Shoemaker\nCouncilor\nGloves Lost\nLost\u2014 Sunday morning a pair of\nlong black silk gloves between Fal\nmouth and the Germantown school\nhouse Finder will please leave them\nat the Outlook office\nMiss Susie Hardin\nOld Iron Rags and Rubber\nI am in the market for old iron rags\nand rubber Will buy all that is\nbrought to me at prices justified by the\nmarket Call and see me\nSamuel Foley\nIce Cream Supper\nThere will be an ice cream supper at\nthe Boyd Presbyterian church Satur\nday night June 6L Proceeds for the\nbenefit of the church AU are invited\nThere will be an excursion to Cincin\nnati May 24 9L25 for the round trip\nTrains leaves Falmouth at 9:Q5 a m\nThe pay of soldiera in the army has\nbeen increased from 919 to 916 per\nmonth for privates All subordinate of\nficers wUl receive additional pay also\nthis new law of Congress\nTbe Scarcity of Cuttle\nThere is a scarcity of cattle in Ken\ntucky aa well as in the great cattle\nproducing states of the West and this\nla primarily responsible for the high\nprice of beef\" said J W Bates ef\nRichmond Ky: Monday\n\"Mr Bates has for years been the\npurchasing agent in Kentucky tar the\nS A S \u00a3o (Schaurtchild A Scheildel\nberg) of New York and buys perhaps\nas many 'fat cattle for the export trade\nas any (nan in the atate Traveling\nabout in different sections of tbe State\nhe has an excellent opportunity to ob\nserve conditions\nLast year when the financial panic\ncame oi\u201d continued Mr Bates \"many\nef the large cattle raisers of the West\nhurried their cattle to market and sold\nthem regardless of price in order to\nturn then) into money before the ex\npected crisis came Consequently the\nWest h4a been pretty well drained of\nits cattik stock Com was fed abun\ndantly to get these cattle ready for\nmarket and now there is a scarcity of\ncom in fnany of the western states\n\"Right now I am told that seed corn\nin Kansas and Nebraska is selling at\nS3 and 6350 per bushel\u2014 not per barrel\nmind yoi but per bushel which to un\nprecedented except when the western\ndrouth several years ago put the price\nup\u201d At ihia figure com to too high to\nfeed the cattle and the grass fed cattle\nare not ready for market While com\nto of course not that high there still\nat $360 knd 94 a barrel' farmers re\ngard it as too valuable to feed to cat\ntie and consequently very few-' are\nready far market but are waiting 1 to\nbe fattened on grass\n\"There are fewer cattle fattened in\nKentucky than in former years Prices\nare away np yonder\u2014 fat export cattle\nbeing quoted at $6 and 6660 per hun\ndred I have engaged a number for\nearly delivery in Madison and adjoining\ncounties at these prices Grass to mine\nabundant and luxuriant than I ever saw\nit In this section and this will have a\ntendency to improve the situation If\nnotfor this fact cattle and beef would\nbe higher than they are I do not look\nfor any decrease in the price of beef\nuntil after tbe grass fed cattle reach\nthe Bifc-kq and the conditions- in the\nWest y-Ser with- the financial ptidn\ngency ilnayiiave the effect of peeping\nup the price v'-\nAlfalfa WUl Save Grain\nA summary of feeding trials by the\nWisconsin station with dairy cows that\nalfalfa can be made to take the place\nof at least one-half of the grain usually\nfed our dairy cows and as the nutri\nents needed by dairy cows can be pro\nduced much more cheaply with alfalfa\nthan with grain the cost of producing\nmilk will be greatly reduced by its' use\nThe cash' returns from feeding this\ncrop at the various experiment stations\nrange from 919 to 990 per ton With\nfour tons per acre these figures show\nexcellent returns from the land devoted\nto alfalfa A conservative estimate\nwould indicate that the dairy farmer\ncan increase hia profits from 60 to 75\nper cent by a liberal but judicious use\nof alfalfa grown upon hia own farm\nAlfalfa can be grown where red clov\ner grows and a good way to get a stand\nis to cut clover in June and keep the\nground in good shape until the middle\nof August and then bow 16 pounds of\ntested alfalfa seed to the acre\n1\nAssessment of The Banks\nIt has been recognised for year! that\ngreat injustice was being done to the\nfranking institutions of Kentucky in\nquiring them to pay tax on a full valu\nation hf their capital surplus and un\ndivided profits while other forma ef\nproperty were 'assessed on an average\nof not more than 60 per cent of their\nvalue For years the banks have been\ntrying to induce the assessing author\nities to place them on something like\nan equal footing with other forma of\nproperty in valuations for taxation but\ntheir representations were ignored and\nthe unequal and unjust assessments\ncontinued At last the State Board of\nValuation under the present adminis\ntration has done what should have been\ndone years ago and have fixed the val\nuation of the bank\u2019s property at 80 per\ncent of the capital surplus and undi\nvided profits This valuation should\nmeet with the hearty approval of every\ncitizen of Kentucky\nIn Bracken eounty Joseph D Han\ncock a tobacco buyer and the farmer\nliving on the Lewis Kinney farm Fri\nday made complaint against CoL in\nlaid's men' stating that they had toned\ntheir horses loose in his pastime and\nthat the soldiers' horses had killed two\nof hto valuable young colts County\nAttorney Kfamey at 'Anguata says that\nif CoL Lillard does not settle with Han\ncoek fbr the colts that suit will ha\nbrought against the State\nTRY\nHam\nMade from selected wheat\nin my own millL When\nyou buy Ideal Roller Mills\u2019\nFlour you are sure of get-\ni i H s w i\nting home-made flour\nV-\nR L GALLOWAY Falmouth Ky\nDAUGHTERS OF AMERICA\nHdl is LniagUe EtictOffic\u2014\nChMMHlhzt\nFlan\nWilliams town was the city chosen as\nthe one in which to hold the annual\nconvention of the Daughters of Ameri\nica the ladies' auxiliary of the Junior\nOrder of United American Mechanics\nat the closing business session held in\nLexington last week\nFrankfort Falmouth and Ashland\nsent representatives there to assist in\nprocmto\u2014'ttie next non sen ties fnr-tbeir\ncity this former making\u2018rqufte\u2019 a hard\nfight but Williamstown wss nearly the\nunanimous choice of the delegation\nMore than 75 delegates representing\nthe 4000 members in Kentucky of the\norder attended the convention\nThe officers for the ensuing year were\nalso chosen There wss considerable\nenthusiasm in the balloting for the of\nficers there being several candidates\nfor every office The result of the\nelection was as follows:\nP 8 C\u2014 Maggie Hendricks\nA Jr P C\u2014 Fannie Steelmen\nState Secretary\u2014 Emma Whiting- -State\nJudiciaries\u2014 H D Johnson and\nHenry Kunnincy Imogen Edwards\nS CL\u2014 Susie Andres -A\n8 C\u2014 Phils Emwine\nS V C -Nellie B Orrill\nA S V C\u2014 Rose Lickert\nS ComL\u2014 Reca Green\nS Warden\u2014 Nora Gentry\n8 Trees\u2014 G W OrrilL\n8 1 S\u2014 May Bromley\n8 O 8\u2014 Frances Stith\nRep Five Years\u2014 William C Fisher\n'The appropriations of this session of\nCongress will almost reach the billion\nmark the expenditures authorised for\nthe coming fiscal year being the great\nest in the history of the United States\nRoller: King Flour\n\nWe gave away over 100\nSamples of our latest\nmake last Friday and we\nhave heard from most of\nthem and all pronounce\nit the BEST\u2014 none better\nALL WE ASK IS A TRIAL\nCoal and Brick For Sale\nDelivered in any part of the town\nChampion Milling Co\n1( J L ROGERS Mga\nfpMMIttlt tttttt1\nNight riders created havoc near\nCampbeltoburg in Henry county Satur\nday night They scraped twenty-eight\ntobacco beds and no one knew of their\nwork until Sunday morning The only\nclew they left waa the tracks of a rubber-tired\nbuggy through Boke Edring\nton\u2019s wheat field A barbwire fence\nwaa cut to give passage for the vehicle\nLaurel Review: There are two kinds\nef girls in Laurel1' Indians also in\nevery town\u2014 the girl that works and\nthe girl that gads T'Commend us to\nthe first named Works lends real\ndlgiitty totha'protty girl\u2018gives her'\ncharm for which there Is no compenaa-j\ntion in idleness She might gad about\nloll on sofas and read novels but she\nprefers to be of some account in the\nworld The girl that works is the salt\nof the earth and of such Is the king\ndom of Heaven The girl that gads\nsoon loses the sweetness and charm of\nyouth and gravitates to boisterousness\nand bad manners\nTired Women\nWomen\u2019s delicate nerve organ\nism suffers much from wprry ex-'\ncitement over-work Headache\nnervousness' backache stomach\ntrouble and general debility are\nthe natural result For all such\nDr Allies\u2019 Nervine will be found\nto be a splendid nerve tonic It\nsoothes the nerves and brings re-\"\nfreshing body-building sleep and\nrest\n\"i have been extremely nervous for\nnoma yeare\u2014Dr Milee Nervine has doa\nme more good than any medicine 1 have\never taken I have used it whenever i\nneeded it and It nlwiw quirted nr\nnerves and etrengtbened ms so that I\nfeel flirt rate\" v\nMRS W H BOZARTH Wamllton Mo\nIf Ant bottle fails to benefit money back i\nMILKS MEDICAL CO Elkhart Ind\nJ\n\n\n\ni\n\ni\n\nr\nr\ne-5\n\nV\n\nt\n1\nvV\n'1","height":"28516","width":"20712"}}
